WEBVTT

00:01.506 --> 00:04.791
You are listening to a message from First Baptist Church, Wichita Falls.

00:05.291 --> 00:14.324
For more information about First Baptist, click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWS.org.

00:14.344 --> 00:17.528
Today's message comes from Senior Pastor, Dr. Bob McCartney.

00:18.770 --> 00:19.411
Hey, good morning.

00:19.451 --> 00:23.296
Welcome to this last installment of Into the Valley.

00:23.336 --> 00:24.658
This is our final

00:24.770 --> 00:27.914
Valley that we're going to walk through this morning.

00:28.355 --> 00:37.668
I want to welcome those of you at Shepherd campus at West Campus and 11 o'clock East glad that you're here today as well as those of you join us online or on television.

00:37.688 --> 00:49.505
Well, let's open our Bibles to Genesis 45 and we're going to talk about walking through the valley of broken relationships this morning.

00:49.865 --> 00:53.330
Maybe there's nothing more painful than

00:53.442 --> 01:05.901
Having a relationship with someone and then there is a moment where either sin or disagreement and sometimes pride comes in and that relationship is severed.

01:06.322 --> 01:13.393
And we want to know, we want to figure out how we walk through the valley of having a broken relationship.

01:13.413 --> 01:19.122
In 2022, there was a story that came from Washington state of Brian Stanley.

01:19.810 --> 01:36.788
Brian spent his youth shuffled back and forth in the foster care system, but after he became an adult, he eventually got a job, he got married, and his wife wanted to know, don't you ever want to know about your sister?

01:37.129 --> 01:40.552
Because he knew that he had had a sister, but he really didn't know she was.

01:40.592 --> 01:44.657
They had got separated in the shuffle of the foster care system in that state.

01:45.397 --> 01:49.682
Well, there was a program in which a person could take a DNA test.

01:50.178 --> 01:54.023
if you were in that system to see if you matched up with someone else.

01:54.124 --> 01:59.611
And so finally at his wife's urging, Brian, took the DNA test.

02:00.312 --> 02:10.447
He sent it in and sure enough, there was another person who was seeking to see if she had a brother and the test came back like a 90% match that they were brother and sister.

02:10.487 --> 02:11.488
So they decided to meet.

02:12.370 --> 02:18.258
They met at a diner, a public place, just somewhere where they could just have a first meeting.

02:18.370 --> 02:20.213
And Rebecca got there first.

02:20.934 --> 02:28.704
She was sitting in a booth and without ever being introduced to him, when Brian walked through the door, she gasped and said, that's him.

02:29.986 --> 02:32.930
Got up, walked across the restaurant, tears are flowing.

02:32.970 --> 02:36.215
They're both embracing before they ever spoke a word.

02:36.916 --> 02:38.958
Well, television station got a hold of that story.

02:40.040 --> 02:44.466
And they went to the diner and there were a bunch of little like the regulars who were in there and they started interviewing them.

02:44.994 --> 02:54.787
And one particular diner who had watched the whole thing unfold said, watching them made me want to make things right with my family.

02:55.729 --> 02:57.211
We love a reunion story.

02:58.112 --> 03:02.658
Those videos of soldiers coming home from a deployment, they get me every time.

03:03.559 --> 03:05.762
We love a reunion story.

03:06.684 --> 03:14.354
And so when it comes to our families, it might not necessarily be reunion, but maybe there needs to be reunification.

03:14.498 --> 03:18.884
Maybe there needs to be reconciliation of some past hurt.

03:19.765 --> 03:29.018
And that's what we're going to explore this morning because in all of our families, there is some tension, there is some awkwardness.

03:29.879 --> 03:33.925
There is that one person that we all wish we could avoid.

03:33.945 --> 03:43.698
And if you don't know who that is in your family, well,

03:44.194 --> 03:45.435
It might be you.

03:48.178 --> 03:56.106
But all of us have those moments at Thanksgiving and at Christmas where we're sort of thrust into difficult situations.

03:57.047 --> 04:05.156
And I think the political divide in our country makes things even a little bit more exacerbated in that relationship.

04:05.696 --> 04:11.442
And so this morning we want to explore how we reconcile broken relationships.

04:13.026 --> 04:18.274
The story that we're going to talk about is the story of a guy named Joseph in the Old Testament.

04:19.015 --> 04:23.041
You need some background before I actually get to our text.

04:23.141 --> 04:24.743
So let me tell you Joseph's story.

04:26.185 --> 04:28.268
Joseph is the son of Jacob.

04:29.390 --> 04:33.056
Jacob the father had 12 sons.

04:34.037 --> 04:40.146
Now that in itself makes for kind of a, you know, a big, difficult family.

04:40.866 --> 04:47.575
But what made it all the more interesting is that those 12 sons had one father, but there were four mothers involved.

04:49.137 --> 04:51.039
They put the fun in dysfunction.

04:51.099 --> 05:08.402
I'll tell you that because there was sibling rivalry always between these brothers and Jacob rather treated Joseph as the favored son, gave him a multicolored coat that nobody else had.

05:08.930 --> 05:12.054
He didn't have to go to work like his brothers most of the time.

05:12.094 --> 05:15.719
They went out tending sheep and Joseph kind of stayed close to home.

05:16.640 --> 05:31.860
And so Jacob created some of this problem and finally it reached such a boiling point that one day Joseph goes out into the pasture to find his brothers who haven't been home in a while and dad suspicious of what they're doing out there.

05:31.900 --> 05:34.404
He goes out to check on them and they say, you know what?

05:34.784 --> 05:36.306
We can get rid of him for good.

05:37.090 --> 05:41.696
There are some Midianite traders that are coming by in a caravan going down to Egypt.

05:41.716 --> 05:43.579
We'll just sell him as a slave.

05:43.599 --> 05:44.380
And that's what they do.

05:45.342 --> 05:47.985
They take their brother and they sell him as a slave.

05:48.726 --> 05:51.130
They go back and tell dad he's died.

05:51.170 --> 05:53.793
They tell him dad he's dead, dad that he's dead.

05:53.813 --> 06:00.983
And so Jacob grieves the loss of Joseph, but the brothers know they sold him as a slave.

06:01.264 --> 06:02.866
They're rid of him forever now.

06:03.746 --> 06:09.976
Well, Joseph is carried down to Egypt where he becomes the slave to an Egyptian general named Potiphar.

06:11.298 --> 06:13.060
And he prospers in Potiphar's house.

06:13.401 --> 06:20.913
He is so efficient, so effective, and so wise, even as a teenager, that Potiphar puts him over his entire household.

06:22.255 --> 06:26.962
But Potiphar's wife has eyes for Joseph and

06:27.330 --> 06:29.473
she tries to lure him and seduce him.

06:29.493 --> 06:36.382
And when he resists her advances, she falsely accuses him of sexual assault and has Joseph thrown in prison.

06:38.085 --> 06:44.874
If it couldn't get worse, Joseph has gone from favored son to slave to now being thrown in prison.

06:46.196 --> 06:55.208
But in prison, Joseph is faithful and he prospers and he's given privileges and the jailer entrusts him with things.

06:55.248 --> 06:56.370
And there he meets

06:57.378 --> 06:59.400
a couple of Pharaoh's servants.

07:01.342 --> 07:04.205
And Joseph has an unusual spiritual gift.

07:04.225 --> 07:05.307
It is very unusual.

07:06.168 --> 07:14.377
He has the ability to listen to someone's dreams and interpret what they mean, especially if this dream came from God.

07:15.518 --> 07:22.385
And so Joseph has this ability and he interprets a dream for this man who was part of Pharaoh's court.

07:24.548 --> 07:26.770
And all that seems good, but when

07:27.074 --> 07:29.898
The official of Pharaoh goes back.

07:30.399 --> 07:31.680
He just forgets about Joseph.

07:32.581 --> 07:34.224
Just forgets about him.

07:34.244 --> 07:37.188
Until one day Pharaoh had a dream.

07:38.289 --> 07:40.853
He had a dream and he didn't know what it meant.

07:40.893 --> 07:41.854
He couldn't interpret it.

07:42.475 --> 07:49.064
And so Joseph is entrusted then to tell Pharaoh what this dream means.

07:50.346 --> 07:55.272
Joseph says to this servant of Pharaoh, I can interpret that dream.

07:55.312 --> 07:56.594
And so the servant

07:56.706 --> 08:07.082
Pharaoh, the court official, Pharaoh takes him and he brings him to Pharaoh's palace and he says, this guy, he told me what my dream man, and he can tell you Pharaoh what your dream means.

08:07.162 --> 08:10.707
And so Pharaoh lays out the dream for Joseph.

08:12.069 --> 08:15.154
And Joseph says, I can tell you what that means.

08:15.394 --> 08:19.699
That means that we're about to enter seven years of an economic boom.

08:20.040 --> 08:21.482
There's going to be prosperity.

08:21.722 --> 08:23.244
There's going to be so much grain.

08:23.284 --> 08:24.425
There's going to be so much food.

08:24.826 --> 08:36.420
But after seven years of this incredible period of prosperity and all of our crops making great harvest, there's going to be seven years of drought and famine and economic depression.

08:37.161 --> 08:41.527
It's going to be so bad that people are going to forget the good years.

08:43.149 --> 08:44.050
Pharaoh listens.

08:44.834 --> 08:46.820
And he says, who could I put in charge of something like this?

08:47.000 --> 08:49.868
Oh, you Joseph, I'll put you in charge of this.

08:50.630 --> 08:52.275
So here's what happens to Joseph summary.

08:52.916 --> 08:57.810
Joseph goes from favored son to slave to prisoner.

08:58.178 --> 09:03.187
All of a sudden, in a matter of moments, Joseph is transported to Pharaoh's palace.

09:03.207 --> 09:10.559
Pharaoh takes off his signet ring, his official symbol of power puts it on Joseph's hand, and he says, you only answer to me.

09:11.020 --> 09:13.384
Everybody else in the kingdom is under your authority.

09:13.865 --> 09:18.012
Basically, Pharaoh says, you are the prime minister of Egypt.

09:19.154 --> 09:20.416
Everybody does what you say.

09:22.460 --> 09:23.922
It took 20 years to get there.

09:24.674 --> 09:29.700
So Genesis 45 is 20 years after his brothers think we are done with Joseph.

09:29.900 --> 09:30.661
He is gone.

09:30.701 --> 09:32.083
We've sold him as a slave.

09:32.743 --> 09:34.826
Slaves didn't live that long in that culture.

09:35.647 --> 09:36.948
He's probably dead by now.

09:37.028 --> 09:38.770
They, they very seldom think of him.

09:41.193 --> 09:48.181
But when the rest of the world started running out of grain, so did Joseph's brothers, but they heard there was grain in Egypt.

09:48.241 --> 09:52.466
And so they go down to Egypt to buy food for their families.

09:53.826 --> 09:54.747
They buy some food.

09:54.787 --> 09:57.992
They see Joseph, but they don't know who Joseph is.

09:58.673 --> 10:00.435
But Joseph recognizes them.

10:00.455 --> 10:04.441
You see, Hebrew shepherds would have had long hair and long beards.

10:04.501 --> 10:06.984
They would have dressed in very plain clothes.

10:08.046 --> 10:09.488
Joseph is now Egyptian.

10:10.349 --> 10:11.610
The Egyptians cut their hair.

10:12.371 --> 10:13.313
They didn't shave.

10:13.393 --> 10:14.975
They plucked their beards.

10:15.135 --> 10:17.138
That sounds very painful to me.

10:17.954 --> 10:21.139
but he would have looked clean shave and his brothers had big beards.

10:21.520 --> 10:24.124
He would have dressed in the clothing of the Egyptians.

10:24.645 --> 10:25.947
They didn't recognize him.

10:26.127 --> 10:29.011
They've long since forgotten him, but Joseph knew them.

10:30.033 --> 10:36.924
So he gave them some test without going so deeply into those because I don't have time to do that to get to the text.

10:38.286 --> 10:43.314
Joseph sends them back and tells them, I want you to bring your younger brother with you.

10:44.994 --> 10:48.339
Now, the younger brother was Joseph's brother with the same mother.

10:49.360 --> 10:53.085
His name was Benjamin, and he loved Benjamin, and he wanted to see Benjamin.

10:53.947 --> 10:56.410
And so, he sends them back.

10:56.470 --> 10:58.593
Well, they delayed, but finally they ran out of food again.

10:58.613 --> 10:59.835
They said, we got to go back down there.

11:00.516 --> 11:02.819
And so they come back and Benjamin is with them.

11:03.500 --> 11:09.409
Now, I want you to imagine, just imagine the emotion that you've been sold like Joseph.

11:09.829 --> 11:11.291
You've been sent to Egypt.

11:11.632 --> 11:13.234
It's been 20 years.

11:13.538 --> 11:19.347
And your brothers walk in and then the youngest of them walks in and immediately you see it in his eyes.

11:19.728 --> 11:20.670
That's Benjamin.

11:21.170 --> 11:22.072
That's your brother.

11:22.372 --> 11:23.454
That's your little brother.

11:25.457 --> 11:35.794
And this is what happens in Genesis 45 verse one, then Joseph could not control himself in front of everyone standing before him.

11:36.130 --> 11:38.974
And he shouted, have everyone leave me?

11:39.354 --> 11:43.419
So there was no one with him when Joseph made himself known to his brothers.

11:44.120 --> 11:48.266
Then he wept so loudly that the Egyptians heard it and the household of Pharaoh heard about it.

11:49.307 --> 11:54.814
And Joseph said to his brothers, I am Joseph.

11:56.076 --> 11:57.438
Is my father still alive?

11:58.539 --> 12:03.986
But his brothers could not answer him, but they were terrified in his presence.

12:05.122 --> 12:06.904
There are people who say they've seen ghost.

12:07.705 --> 12:08.746
I don't necessarily believe that.

12:10.048 --> 12:11.750
But it's as if they saw a ghost.

12:11.770 --> 12:13.111
They thought he's long gone.

12:13.892 --> 12:16.055
They haven't thought about Joseph.

12:16.075 --> 12:20.179
And when they did, they tried to put it out of their minds for their guilt over what they'd done to him.

12:21.301 --> 12:27.848
And now he's standing in front of them and he has the authority, the power of life and death over them.

12:30.411 --> 12:32.754
And Joseph takes five steps.

12:33.570 --> 12:38.697
in this passage that I want you to see that are steps to reconcile a broken relationship.

12:38.938 --> 12:39.899
Here's step number one.

12:41.001 --> 12:44.426
Don't publicly err your dirty laundry.

12:45.868 --> 12:48.031
Don't publicly err your dirty laundry.

12:49.032 --> 12:50.775
Joseph clears the room.

12:51.837 --> 12:58.386
That means all of the Egyptian officials who were there to attend to him, who were record keepers or

12:58.530 --> 13:01.072
who took the money for the grain that people were buying.

13:01.513 --> 13:02.894
All of those people are sent out.

13:03.154 --> 13:12.243
If there were other people along with the brothers who were there to buy grain, because the whole world starving to death because of this famine, if there were others, they were sent out.

13:12.563 --> 13:15.206
It is Joseph and his brothers.

13:16.007 --> 13:17.728
He is there alone with them.

13:18.329 --> 13:19.450
Why is that important?

13:20.331 --> 13:27.858
Because this deliberate act of privacy is also an act of mercy.

13:28.642 --> 13:34.328
Joseph had the right to shame them, to expose them.

13:34.788 --> 13:41.135
Joseph had the right to get revenge on them and say, no, I won't sell you any grain after what you did to me.

13:41.816 --> 13:51.165
I won't sell you any food, but Joseph chooses in this moment to make this moment of reconciliation private.

13:52.106 --> 13:55.570
You see, reconciliation thrives in an environment.

13:56.194 --> 13:59.338
where the other person's dignity is protected.

14:00.820 --> 14:15.899
Dignity protected opens the door for forgiveness and for a relationship to begin to flourish again, to have that moment when the seeds of a relationship can begin to grow again.

14:16.780 --> 14:21.967
Michael Reagan was the adopted son of President Reagan and his first wife.

14:22.788 --> 14:24.530
Before he became a Christian and when

14:24.642 --> 14:25.983
President Reagan was elected.

14:26.083 --> 14:28.005
Michael Reagan wrote a book.

14:28.025 --> 14:34.892
And it was one of those tell-all books where they tell the dirty laundry and the family secrets and all those things that happened behind closed doors.

14:35.712 --> 14:39.716
About three years later, he got saved, became a Christian.

14:40.777 --> 14:52.148
And when he became a Christian, he suddenly realized that that book that he had written was so offensive, that he went back to the publisher and he asked them to never print a second printing of that first book.

14:52.428 --> 14:54.450
He wrote a second book called Twice Adopted.

14:55.330 --> 15:00.616
that was printed, but he left out all of those other salacious stories that he had told in the first book.

15:01.177 --> 15:06.644
Michael Reagan said, writing that first book was the biggest mistake of my life.

15:07.525 --> 15:13.612
I wounded the very people I love because I made private pain public.

15:15.534 --> 15:20.581
So if you want to reconcile a relationship, the first step is don't air your dirty laundry.

15:21.081 --> 15:25.106
Avoid confronting people in front of others.

15:25.218 --> 15:29.183
Don't drag the rest of the family into your drama.

15:29.784 --> 15:34.951
Don't post on Wednesday before the gathering at grandma's on Thursday for Thanksgiving.

15:35.211 --> 15:39.336
How much you dread going in there with your cousins because they're such terrible people.

15:40.017 --> 15:43.001
That is not the way to reconcile a relationship.

15:44.343 --> 15:46.766
Often we feel like, you know what, I need to state my case.

15:46.826 --> 15:50.090
I need to make sure everybody knows that I was the one who was wronged.

15:51.552 --> 15:53.074
That's never going

15:53.346 --> 15:56.289
to be the winning recipe for reconciling a relationship.

15:56.649 --> 16:03.315
Jesus said in Matthew 18, 15, if your brother sins, go and show him his fault.

16:03.516 --> 16:03.936
Look at this.

16:04.797 --> 16:09.261
In private, if he listens to you, you've won your brother.

16:09.882 --> 16:14.286
So the first step is don't publicly air your dirty laundry.

16:14.746 --> 16:18.470
Deal with whatever matter you have to deal with in private.

16:19.130 --> 16:23.154
Second, don't play the blame game.

16:23.682 --> 16:25.384
Don't play the blame game.

16:25.484 --> 16:26.245
Look at verse four.

16:27.105 --> 16:29.828
Joseph said to his brothers, please come closer to me.

16:30.429 --> 16:31.510
And they came closer.

16:31.590 --> 16:34.272
And he said, I am your brother, Joseph.

16:35.934 --> 16:37.015
And now I'm going to prove it.

16:37.836 --> 16:40.579
Whom you sold to Egypt.

16:41.760 --> 16:43.261
That's not somebody pretending to be Joseph.

16:43.281 --> 16:45.043
That was a detail that only he would know.

16:45.103 --> 16:52.210
Now do not be grieved or angry with yourselves because you sold me here.

16:52.610 --> 16:56.775
For God sent me ahead of you to save lives.

16:57.676 --> 16:58.757
I want you to notice something.

16:59.117 --> 16:59.858
This is important.

17:00.739 --> 17:04.243
Joseph did not sweep their behavior under the rug.

17:04.504 --> 17:07.567
He didn't pretend it didn't happen.

17:08.068 --> 17:10.210
He even doesn't pretend that it didn't hurt.

17:11.392 --> 17:14.015
He acknowledges his own hurt.

17:14.575 --> 17:18.920
You are the ones who sold me as a slave into Egypt.

17:19.561 --> 17:20.562
But notice this.

17:20.866 --> 17:26.976
He reframes everything under the providence of God.

17:28.157 --> 17:34.087
You sold me, but God sent me in verse seven.

17:35.569 --> 17:43.461
So God sent me ahead of you to ensure for you a remnant on the earth to keep you alive by great deliverance.

17:43.922 --> 17:49.010
Now therefore, it was not you who sent me here, but God,

17:50.114 --> 18:01.670
You see, Joseph has reached a place of looking back on his hurt when he can say, good came out of the pain I endured.

18:02.651 --> 18:09.921
Forgiveness becomes possible when I look for and see the hand of God in my hurt.

18:10.642 --> 18:12.465
It's not saying the hurt's not real.

18:13.606 --> 18:16.931
It's not like we're acting like something didn't happen.

18:17.552 --> 18:19.154
But what we're saying is,

18:19.650 --> 18:29.984
that we choose providence over bitterness, we choose purpose over punishment, and we choose redemption over resentment."

18:30.004 --> 18:31.106
No, it's an amazing thing.

18:32.648 --> 18:42.962
But when there's some memory of a past hurt, it's amazing how often those things pop up.

18:44.386 --> 18:45.588
You know, I don't even think about it.

18:45.608 --> 18:47.631
I don't even think about a person sometimes.

18:47.691 --> 19:01.190
And then all of a sudden that old hurt, that old offense, that old moment when they said something or they did something or they hurt someone very close to me, whom I love, whom I thought that they should have never said that about or done that to.

19:01.551 --> 19:05.296
Those old memories begin to re-flood back into my life.

19:05.496 --> 19:10.123
I need to refuse to rehearse that over and over in my mind.

19:11.044 --> 19:12.306
And I need to refuse

19:12.738 --> 19:18.727
to assume the worst motives about those that I'm trying to be reconciled with.

19:19.248 --> 19:24.516
Most of the time, we see others in the worst light possible.

19:24.556 --> 19:26.379
We see ourselves in the best light possible.

19:28.001 --> 19:39.598
We think our motives were pretty pure, but our cousin that did that to us or that family member that offended and hurt us, we see them in the worst possible light.

19:40.760 --> 19:42.002
Joseph chooses

19:42.146 --> 19:44.269
to refuse to play the blame game.

19:44.289 --> 19:53.762
2015, Dylan Ruth walked into the Immanuel AME Church in Charleston, South Carolina.

19:53.782 --> 19:55.205
A Bible study was going on.

19:55.405 --> 19:57.768
I think there were 13 people there.

19:58.549 --> 20:00.091
He walked in, they welcomed him in.

20:01.173 --> 20:08.804
Now, the Immanuel AME Church is a majority black church, and Dylan Ruth was a white guy.

20:08.824 --> 20:10.386
But they welcomed him in.

20:11.074 --> 20:13.278
started talking to him.

20:13.298 --> 20:21.711
But after a few minutes, Dylan Roof pulled out a firearm and opened fire and he killed nine people in that church, in that Bible study.

20:23.294 --> 20:32.329
And the amazing thing is that when the time came for him to be sentenced, or to be arraigned, there were people there who spoke.

20:33.571 --> 20:38.098
One gentleman stood up and he said, I refuse

20:38.402 --> 20:42.746
to let hate write the final chapter, I forgive you.

20:44.027 --> 20:52.115
Nadine Collier, who was wounded, said, you took something very precious from me, but I forgive you.

20:53.537 --> 21:07.250
One of the things that we have to do as followers of Jesus is to refuse to allow hate and bitterness and resentment to color the way that we see other people around us.

21:08.482 --> 21:10.927
We are to be the people who are the forgivers.

21:12.249 --> 21:14.614
We're the, we're to be the people who forgive first.

21:16.337 --> 21:22.229
That's who we're called to be, to model for people what our Savior has done for us.

21:23.531 --> 21:29.202
Now I'm going to be honest with you, I, I wrestle with this part of this passage this week because I, I'm like you.

21:30.466 --> 21:43.185
I mean, I don't know where it comes from, but out of the blue, one of those old memories will come back of someone who did something very hurtful in my life, people who've questioned my motives, people who've said sometimes horrible things, who don't even know me.

21:44.346 --> 21:50.195
And sometimes, you know, this old desire for revenge begins to boil in you.

21:51.437 --> 21:55.303
And it's hard not to act on that.

21:55.363 --> 21:57.586
It's hard not to dwell on that.

21:57.858 --> 22:00.182
But I want to tell you there's no peace in that.

22:00.522 --> 22:01.884
It will steal your joy.

22:01.924 --> 22:04.388
It will suck the life out of you.

22:04.849 --> 22:07.392
If you allow it to dominate you, don't play the blame game.

22:08.234 --> 22:13.582
Number three, do welcome them back into your life.

22:13.622 --> 22:14.623
Look at verse nine.

22:15.645 --> 22:16.306
Hurry.

22:16.546 --> 22:28.558
and go up to my Father and say to Him, this is what your son Joseph says, God has made me Lord of all Egypt, come down to me, do not delay, for you shall live in the land of Goshen."

22:28.578 --> 22:29.999
That's the best land in Egypt.

22:30.820 --> 22:39.448
He says, you shall be near me, you and your children and grandchildren and your flocks and your herds and all you have come down to me.

22:39.468 --> 22:41.950
You shall be near me.

22:41.990 --> 22:45.714
This is an act of brotherly love.

22:46.562 --> 22:51.389
Joseph acts out of the knowledge that he has.

22:52.290 --> 22:56.275
One of the things he tells them is, look, you think this famine's bad now?

22:56.455 --> 22:59.640
We're only two years in and there's five more years to go.

22:59.960 --> 23:02.343
You got to come down here so I can take care of you.

23:03.565 --> 23:08.111
Joseph makes the move to welcome them back into his life.

23:09.032 --> 23:14.179
Now, look, the restoration of a relationship is complicated.

23:14.860 --> 23:16.082
I want to acknowledge that.

23:16.578 --> 23:20.523
I'm not telling you that these five steps will be immediate or easy.

23:21.344 --> 23:22.786
And I also want to address this.

23:23.547 --> 23:29.234
While we are called as Christians, we are commanded as Christians to extend forgiveness.

23:29.334 --> 23:33.079
Forgiveness is not optional obedience for a follower of Jesus.

23:34.441 --> 23:39.287
Reconciling a relationship is another step and I want to acknowledge this.

23:40.168 --> 23:44.594
Sometimes it is neither possible nor wise.

23:46.050 --> 23:55.039
If there was abuse involved, it may well not be wise to reconcile a relationship.

23:55.140 --> 23:56.841
Forgiveness is not an option.

23:58.863 --> 24:07.252
But reconciliation requires all parties to come to the table.

24:07.272 --> 24:12.658
And when someone denies their culpability, when they are unrepentant,

24:13.794 --> 24:18.019
It is going to be very difficult to reconcile a relationship.

24:18.800 --> 24:32.577
So while reconciliation is not always wise or possible, what we need to do in most situations, because there are relationships that should be restored, is to reopen that door gently.

24:34.119 --> 24:35.320
Here's what most of us do.

24:36.782 --> 24:40.186
We don't really reconcile relationships.

24:40.206 --> 24:43.410
We just settle for a ceasefire.

24:43.490 --> 24:44.992
at grandma's at Thanksgiving.

24:46.434 --> 24:54.946
We just settled for keeping our mouths closed and enduring the three hours or four hours that were there.

24:55.487 --> 25:01.676
And then we are set free until at least Christmas and then we're set free until the Fourth of July.

25:03.819 --> 25:07.865
That's the way a lot of our families function or may I say dysfunction.

25:10.028 --> 25:11.570
But there's something better.

25:12.706 --> 25:15.329
And that is rebuilding a relationship.

25:15.910 --> 25:21.658
In 2019, there was a social media post that kind of went viral about a dad in Oklahoma.

25:21.678 --> 25:26.904
Her names were withheld because the dad didn't want the story told with his son's name in it.

25:27.005 --> 25:37.779
But his son got involved in substance abuse, started stealing to fund his habit, and eventually he stole his dad's pickup truck.

25:38.239 --> 25:40.402
Well, the dad didn't want to report it stolen.

25:40.610 --> 25:44.194
He was trying to reach out to his son, but the son never came back.

25:45.255 --> 25:51.543
And finally his insurance agent told him, look, you need to report this truck stolen or you'll be liable for whatever happens in it.

25:52.484 --> 25:55.788
And so the dad reluctantly reported the truck stolen.

25:56.749 --> 26:07.762
Well, about six months later, the son was arrested and he had several warrants out on him for things, a drug possession and things like that.

26:07.938 --> 26:11.502
the police officer who makes the arrest runs the warrant.

26:11.522 --> 26:12.924
He's driving a stolen truck.

26:13.004 --> 26:14.906
So he's arrested for driving a stolen truck too.

26:15.647 --> 26:24.336
So they put him in the orange jumpsuit and handcuffs and send him back to his hometown to the county seat where he lived about two hours away from where he was, was arrested.

26:25.338 --> 26:26.839
And the judge knew the dad.

26:27.400 --> 26:28.761
So the dad's sitting in the courtroom.

26:29.903 --> 26:35.389
And so the judge says on the day these are going to be arraigned, does the dad have anything to say?

26:35.409 --> 26:36.370
And the dad stood up

26:37.186 --> 26:39.348
There was a good bit of tension in the courtroom in that moment.

26:39.368 --> 26:41.190
They're like, is he gonna blast his son?

26:41.230 --> 26:42.831
Tell him how disappointed he is in him?

26:43.692 --> 26:48.256
The father stands up and he says, I want all the charges dropped.

26:49.878 --> 26:51.119
I want you to drop all the charges.

26:51.159 --> 26:57.185
Now, they could drop the charge on the stolen truck because that was the dad's doing.

26:57.205 --> 26:58.806
But the drug charges had to stand.

26:59.907 --> 27:05.112
But he told the judge, judge, I don't want to punish him.

27:05.152 --> 27:06.834
I want to rebuild him.

27:07.938 --> 27:14.105
Now that might be naive for a father of a young man who's addicted to substances, right?

27:15.246 --> 27:17.890
But it is the proof of a father's love.

27:19.832 --> 27:32.146
And it's the way you reconcile a relationship, not by dishing out punishment for the hurt that someone put you through, but by rebuilding the relationship from the ground up.

27:32.802 --> 27:35.606
Number four, give people unexpected blessings.

27:35.666 --> 27:43.697
The fourth step, if you want to reconcile a relationship, after you've gone through those first three steps, do give people unexpected blessings.

27:43.717 --> 27:44.638
Look at verse 16.

27:45.860 --> 27:53.350
Now when the news was heard in Pharaoh's house that Joseph's brothers had come, now they're there, it pleased Pharaoh and his servants.

27:53.370 --> 27:55.954
Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, say to your brothers, do this.

27:56.034 --> 28:01.880
Load your livestock, go to the land of Canaan, and take your father and your household, and come to me.

28:01.920 --> 28:06.065
I'll give you the best land of Egypt, and you will eat at the fat of the land.

28:06.546 --> 28:12.392
Now you are ordered, do this, take wagons from the land of Egypt for your little ones, for your wives, and bring your father and come.

28:12.933 --> 28:15.235
And do not concern yourselves with your property.

28:15.515 --> 28:19.300
For the best of all the land of Egypt is yours."

28:22.123 --> 28:25.106
They're about to receive an incredible

28:25.186 --> 28:32.096
Blessing, Joseph's family is given the very best land possible to graze their flocks.

28:32.697 --> 28:40.589
They will be provided with abundant food in a time of tremendous famine all over the known world at that time.

28:41.250 --> 28:43.794
Joseph's family is going to be taken care of.

28:44.094 --> 28:48.440
You see, grace doesn't offer the minimum just to get by.

28:48.821 --> 28:53.468
Grace always offers extravagance.

28:53.488 --> 28:54.930
It goes above and beyond.

28:56.002 --> 29:00.207
And that's what we see a picture of in this moment.

29:00.227 --> 29:07.336
Maybe there's a peace offering that you could extend to that person in your family to reconcile this relationship.

29:07.736 --> 29:09.719
Maybe you could go above and beyond.

29:11.601 --> 29:22.134
Douglas County, Colorado Deputy Sheriff Cody Hubbard was out on patrol about a year ago when he was following a car that had expired plates.

29:23.756 --> 29:25.458
Deputy Hubbard pulls the car over.

29:26.370 --> 29:27.811
talks to the lady who's in it.

29:28.632 --> 29:29.493
She's unemployed.

29:29.573 --> 29:30.594
She's a single mom.

29:31.115 --> 29:34.978
She can't pay to have the car, the license renewed on the car.

29:35.899 --> 29:38.382
And he says to her, I tell you what I want you to do.

29:38.622 --> 29:41.004
I want you to get back in the car and I want you to follow me.

29:41.805 --> 29:43.527
Reluctantly, she didn't know what was going to happen.

29:43.587 --> 29:52.956
She followed him and he drove straight to the DMV where he walked in with her and out of his own wallet, he pulled out the money to pay to have her car renewed.

29:54.217 --> 29:55.058
Grace

29:55.234 --> 29:57.899
goes above and beyond what is required.

29:58.019 --> 30:04.591
Grace offers an extravagant offering to say, let's make this right together.

30:05.332 --> 30:06.835
Do give people unexpected blessings.

30:06.895 --> 30:09.860
And finally, do take the initiative.

30:11.303 --> 30:13.446
Joseph didn't wait for an apology.

30:14.568 --> 30:17.714
This is our biggest problem in reconciling relationships.

30:18.498 --> 30:25.208
We always think that other person's going to come around to my way of thinking they're going to see it my way.

30:25.248 --> 30:27.511
They're going to come to me and ask me for forgiveness.

30:29.414 --> 30:30.215
Read the text.

30:30.696 --> 30:35.764
Joseph's brothers never asked him for forgiveness for what they did to him.

30:35.944 --> 30:36.505
They didn't.

30:38.167 --> 30:41.472
Joseph takes the initiative anyway.

30:42.173 --> 30:48.242
He refuses to let pride or fear or that old hurt.

30:48.994 --> 30:51.818
Keep him from making the relationship right.

30:52.779 --> 30:54.041
So here's my challenge to you.

30:55.763 --> 31:10.824
Send that text, make that phone call, make it private, make it pointed, get to the point, but tell them the relationship matters than the past hurt.

31:12.606 --> 31:13.848
Take the initiative.

31:14.128 --> 31:15.010
Why should you do that?

31:17.093 --> 31:18.194
Because that's the gospel.

31:20.482 --> 31:23.966
You see, in the story of the gospel, we're not Joseph.

31:25.467 --> 31:26.148
We're the brothers.

31:28.130 --> 31:29.632
We're the offending party.

31:31.354 --> 31:42.265
But God, being rich in mercy extends grace toward us because of his love for us.

31:42.766 --> 31:44.468
Here's the way Paul put it in the book of Romans.

31:45.649 --> 31:50.194
But while we were still sinners, Christ

31:50.306 --> 31:51.928
died for us.

31:54.791 --> 32:20.082
While we were still sinners, Christ made the choice to go to a cross, to pay our price, to die a death we deserved and to extend to us the offer of reconciling a relationship between sinful people like us

32:20.322 --> 32:21.523
and a holy God.

32:23.045 --> 32:27.210
He became the mediator between a holy God and sinful people.

32:28.711 --> 32:34.838
He took the initiative to take your sins and mine on that cross so that we could be forgiven.

32:36.760 --> 32:44.589
If there is anything that should prompt us toward gratitude, it is that singular thought.

32:46.251 --> 32:49.234
If we move toward Thanksgiving, if there is anything

32:50.338 --> 32:54.765
that should move us toward being so grateful to God.

32:56.568 --> 33:07.065
It is that He chose not to overlook the offense, but to pay the price for the offense so that we could be reconciled to God.

33:09.809 --> 33:13.655
You've been listening to a message from First Baptist Church, Wichita Falls.

33:13.675 --> 33:18.002
For more information about First Baptist, including gathering times and locations,

33:18.146 --> 33:22.278
Click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWF.org.

33:22.661 --> 33:23.890
We'll see you next week.

